# The Machine

For all experiments, there is a warmup time, when more and more energy is being fed into the machine. (human)

There are adjustable controls for the characters to set: how far in space the teleport goes (distance from the machine), and how "far" in multiverse the teleport goes (i.e. how many adjacent universes get hopped). (human)

The machine can only communicate forward along the line of universes; they cannot communicate backwards. (human)

The multiverses are arranged along a 1-dimensional line. There is an adjacent universe forward and behind the current universe. (human)

With more power (or some kind of adjustable control), they can communicate with universe 2, 3, 4, etc. universes ahead. They can never communicate behind. (human)

We don't know if there is an infinite number of universes or a finite amount. (human)

